President Jacob Zuma&#8217;s office has confirmed that he has filed papers in the High Court in Pretoria in an attempt to set aside the former Public Protector&#8217;s State of Capture report.Thuli Madonsela&#8217;s report was released to the public in November. It detailed an intricate relationship between President Zuma and his son, Duduzane, with the Gupta family.Several ministers and heads of state-owned enterprises were also implicated in the report.President Zuma&#8217;s Spokesperson, Dr Bongani Ngqulunga explains, Yes, I can confirm that President Jacob Zuma has lodged an application with the High Court of South Africa to review and set aside the remedial action contained in the State of Capture report. The president is also asking the court to refer the matter back to the public protector for further investigation. You will recall that, I think it was over a week ago, the Presidency issued a statement that the president will take the State of Capture report to curt for review, and so yesterday the president did that. -SABC